The paper discusses a biologically-inspired research agenda aimed at AI and AI safety, which involves building biophysically realistic simulations of simple organisms and grounding AI goal structures in neuropsychology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
